The last few years, family photos were hard. There was always a baby that should have been there but wasn’t. I was so excited for Christmas photos this year because our precious miracle is here! She’s here! I still can’t believe it! Thank you, Jesus! Merry Christmas to each and every one of you! Love, the Ngs ❤️ #merrychristmas #christmas #family #familyphotos #happyholidays

2022...the year we saw God change everything!❤️ Having 7 babies in heaven, we weren’t sure what this past year would bring. Choosing faith over fear was minute by minute, every single day. When we shared at the beginning of 2022 that we were pregnant, I went into our room and cried. The “what if’s” and fear came rushing in. I just wanted time to speed up so I could hold our baby in my arms. That’s the image I kept in my mind. The moment I would hear her cry, feel her weight on my chest and that we would have our baby! May 19th, that day came! The fight was over and Ariella Capri was here! She’s our miracle and we are beyond thankful that God answered our prayers! Camden and Bella are the best big brother and sister and what a joy it has been having our family of 5 this year! 2022.. we will never forget you. 2023...you’ve got a lot to top! Happy New Years! 🎆🥂❤️ #newyears #nye #2022 #2023 #recurrentmiscarriage #hyperfertility #familyof5

She loves mangos and peaches and teething crackers. She doesn’t like sippy cups but she loves her mommy’s drinking glasses. She likes to sit on her mat and play with her toys. She loves it when everyone makes her laugh. She waves bye bye. She has three teeth! 

Happy 8 months, Ariella! We love you further than the moon and back!

Last Mother’s Day, I was so scared and full of anxiety. We were so close to Ariella’s arrival but I couldn’t shake the fear and worry that something was going to happen. I remember standing in the kitchen with my husband and sobbing and saying that we should go to the hospital and get her out.  I spent almost 40 weeks living in fear every second the day and it was becoming unbearable. Being a part of a recurrent miscarriage support group, you hear the most heartbreaking experiences. I knew I wouldn’t be okay until she was in my arms. The what ifs were getting so scary. This Friday, Ariella turns one! I can’t tell you how extremely healing this past year has been for my family and I! And today, I celebrated Mother’s Day as a mama of 3 ( and another 7 in heaven). We prayed so hard for years for this! God’s plans are so much better than our own. He was with us every single step of the way. He was in all the details, the tears and the crying out for him to stop the storm. To all the women out there that are going through a hard journey to become a mother,  I know that our Heavenly Father can do anything and most importantly …what seems like the impossible. I am praying for your arms to be full and for your chest to feel the weight of a precious gift from God! To all the mothers, Happy Mother’s Day! If anything, these past handful of years has taught me that our children are truly MIRACLES! We all are! Being a mother is such a beautiful gift! 🌸 #happymothersday #mothersday #recurrentmiscarriage #miscarriage #Godisgood #ariellacapring

If only peonies lasted longer…here are some hacks to get the longest vase life! 
Garden:
*Cut peonies with sharp shears or scissors.
*Shake peonies upside down to get the ants out or you can place them upside down in cold water and the ants will come out. 
*Place peonies in a bucket of water. 
*Add ice cubes 
*Place bucket of peonies in the shade or cool spot until ready to vase. 
 
Vase:
*Fill vase with cold water (warm water if you want the peonies to open).
*Add ice cubes.
*Add sugar
*Add sparkling water or vinegar 
*Cut off leaves and cut stem at an angle.
*Refresh water every two days. 
*Store in cool dark place at night.
*Keep out of direct sunlight.
ENJOY!!!!

I’ve been making these cookies for years and I originally found the recipe on the back of the Trader Joe’s Oats bag! I will say, I do a few things differently, but these cookies are a HUGE hit and big crowd pleaser! Probably, my lost asked recipe! So here it is! 

Ingredients:
1/4 cup butter (dairy free can be used too)
3/4 cup organic sugar 
3/4 cup organic brown sugar 
2 organic eggs 
1 tsp organic vanilla extract
1 1/4 tsp baking soda 
1 cup organic peanut butter 
3 cups of organic rolled oats (I like the One Degree brand) 
6 ounces of dairy free chocolate chips and more if you like CHOCOLATE! 
*you don’t have to use organic ingredients. 

Instructions:
In a large bowl combine butter, sugar and brown sugar and beat until creamy. Add eggs, vanilla and baking soda and mix well. Add peanut butter and mix. Stir in oats and chocolate chips. Refrigerate 1-2 hours. Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Roll dough into balls, place on parchment or silicone baking sheets and bake for 10-12 minutes.
